Remarks: There is little doubt that the present material from New Caledonia is conspecific with the specimens with distinctly sinuated hydrothecal margins from French Polynesia examined by Vervoort & Vasseur (1977 , as
H. buskii
) and, subsequently, by Schuchert (1997 , provisionally assigned to
H. polymorpha
). Their main morphological and morphometrical features are compared in Table 5 . Unfortunately, it was not possible to obtain the material of Vervoort & Vassueur for a re-examination, due to ongoing renovation of NBC.

1) 
Schuchert (1997)
stated that, occasionally, these may occur in pairs behind the hydrocladial hydrothecae, a conclusion confirmed by our observations;

Distribution: New Caledonia (present study), French Polynesia ( Vervoort & Vasseur, 1977 ; as
H. buskii
).
